column19: doctor_notes
Patient presents with redness, discharge, and itching in both eyes. Conjunctival injection observed. Prescribed antibiotic eye drops.
Patient complains of gradual vision loss and increased intraocular pressure. Disc cupping and visual field defects noted. Initiated glaucoma treatment.
Patient reports cloudy vision, difficulty in seeing at night. Opacities in the lens observed. Recommended cataract surgery.
Emergency case with sudden onset of flashes and floaters, visual field loss. Fundoscopy reveals retinal tear and detachment. Urgent surgery scheduled.
Elderly patient with central vision loss. Amsler grid test shows distortion. Diagnosis: Age-related macular degeneration. Started anti-VEGF therapy.
Patient complains of burning, itching, and dryness in both eyes. Schirmer's test indicates decreased tear production. Prescribed artificial tears.
Patient experienced foreign body sensation, tearing, and pain after trauma. Slit lamp exam reveals corneal abrasion. Treated with antibiotic ointment and patching.
Patient reports redness, discharge, and eye discomfort. Signs of viral conjunctivitis. Advised supportive care and isolation.
Seasonal eye itching and redness. No signs of infection. Prescribed antihistamine eye drops and advised allergen avoidance.
Diabetic patient with retinal hemorrhages and microaneurysms. Recommended close monitoring and control of blood sugar levels.
Pediatric patient with misalignment of eyes. Orthoptic evaluation reveals esotropia. Refer to a pediatric ophthalmologist for further assessment.
